<br>
First of all, post 4 in this thread mentions &quot;If non-Fed want in on our action, they can join one of our guilds.&quot;<br>
<br>
Because most of the time they are devoted to the guild, is why they dont join the guild. Which brings another point. NSoG has its own NsoG only raids. if you want some raids to be fed only, make it private in the first place. <br>
<br>
Now IMO, the mentioning of &quot;If a raid is being conducted, and it is open to everyone, Fed and non-Fed, I will not support the raid and I will ask members of Unhomed to do the same. &quot;<br>
so be it. why dont we ALL not support raids that dont affect certain people only? Because it is not what eq is for. people can do what they wish, but doesnt that seem a bit rude? after all, raids are for FUN!!! Not loot, cash, xp, only fun. If someone gets something out of it, so be it. Congratulate them and move on.<br>
<br>
next in line: &quot;leave fed raids to fed members&quot;<br>
<br>
yet again, open raids and fed only raids are a must in that situation. <br>
RP and NSoG allow other non members to be in their raids, why shouldnt fed? I doubt we deny ANYONE from signing up. If it comes down to too many people, cut the people as the raid leader sees fit, in terms of classes needed, levels, and fed/non fed status. <br>
<br>
Example: I am a 44th IKS/SHD. Very common class, but not common race for it. Now, say i sign up for a fed fear raid at 47. God forbid, a non fed member signing up on a fed raid.<br>
do you A.) disallow mefrom coming to the raid regardless, or B.) depending upon the people signed up, remove me from the list if need be, depending upon levs,classes, and alliance status. <br>
If i go, 9 times out of 10 i would be the only iks/shd there. when you pull the nightmares in fear, there is another situation: Greenmist armor drops... iks/shd only. What do you do then? its a decision of the raid leaders depending upon the situation at hand. <br>
<br>
moving on then...<br>
to the &quot;uber/elitist&quot; section.<br>
I dont consider myself Uber or Elitist in any case. the best item i have is the Greenmist, which questing was a living hell for me, but i still earned it, and i dont regret sacrificing the levels and time. Personally i have not ran into any uber or elitist attitudes here. I respect the people here, which is the major difference between the feds and Triton or FoH. The 2 guilds in question everyone is downright RUDE! because with power comes responsibility, like peter parker's uncle said. However, imo, the &quot;uber guilds&quot; have turned that power into arrogance and corruption, in which i have a lack of respect for. The reason im not in an uber guild aside from levs? I like to keep a certain amount of honor. Honor as being a noble race in EQ, honor as staying with RP through good and bad, and honor in dropping everything to help another, I.E. Cancelling my trip to a pickup vox raid to help and collect people for melobolgia with the glowing cliff golem for his greenmist quest. <br>
<br>
I dont mean anyone disrespect in any way here. I have never kept an enemy in EQ, except maybe dheynos, but that was my own character on veeshan server, so he doesnt count. I just needed to explain some things. Let the flaming of me commence when ready, im personally expecting at least 1 thing. but that will not change my opinion. You are my friends and allies, lets keep it that way <p>*cuts the engines and rides the wind... the patented "Dino Bird Swoop"*
<p>
Chan, Resident Sexah Leezard,
<p>
 Proud Officer, Risen Phoenix, Povar Server

